                            <comment id="371494" author="stancheff" created="Mon, 8 May 2023 11:31:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16739&quot; title=&quot;sanity 400b fails due to recent lustre_disk.h changes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16739&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16739&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;uapi: make lustre_disk.h buildable in user land&quot;) applied the user space compile failure when 6.4 kernel-headers are installed is resolved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately we get a new issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/include/uapi/linux/lustre/lustre_disk.h:410:2: error: unknown type name &#8216;uuid_le&#8217;
&#160; 410 | &#160;uuid_le sf_uuid; &#160; &#160; &#160;/* 128-bit uuid for volume */
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160;^~~~~~~ &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If including the new header &amp;lt;linux/mei_uuid.h&amp;gt; resolves the above, however a new problem appears due to guid_t and uuid_le not being the same type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/obdclass/scrub.c: In function &#8216;scrub_file_to_cpu&#8217;:
/home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/obdclass/scrub.c:50:12: error: passing argument 1 of &#8216;guid_copy&#8217; from incompatible pointer type [-Werror=incompatible-pointer-types]
&#160; &#160;50 | &#160;guid_copy(&amp;amp;des-&amp;gt;sf_uuid, &amp;amp;src-&amp;gt;sf_uuid);
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;^~~~~~~~~~~~~
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;|
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;uuid_le * {aka struct &amp;lt;anonymous&amp;gt; *}
In file included from /home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/include/lustre_scrub.h:36,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/obdclass/scrub.c:38:
include/linux/uuid.h:51:38: note: expected &#8216;guid_t *&#8217; {aka &#8216;struct &amp;lt;anonymous&amp;gt; *&#8217;} but argument is of type &#8216;uuid_le *&#8217; {aka &#8216;struct &amp;lt;anonymous&amp;gt; *&#8217;}
&#160; &#160;51 | static inline void guid_copy(guid_t *dst, const guid_t *src)
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;~~~~~~~~^~~
/home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/obdclass/scrub.c:50:27: error: passing argument 2 of &#8216;guid_copy&#8217; from incompatible pointer type [-Werror=incompatible-pointer-types]
&#160; &#160;50 | &#160;guid_copy(&amp;amp;des-&amp;gt;sf_uuid, &amp;amp;src-&amp;gt;sf_uuid);
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ^~~~~~~~~~~~~
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; |
&#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; uuid_le * {aka struct &amp;lt;anonymous&amp;gt; *}
In file included from /home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/include/lustre_scrub.h:36,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;from /home/shaun/lustre-release/lustre/obdclass/scrub.c:38:
 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="371485" author="stancheff" created="Mon, 8 May 2023 01:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is resolved in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16739&quot; title=&quot;sanity 400b fails due to recent lustre_disk.h changes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16739&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16739&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; switching to uuid_le&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
